        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process for tour J09D:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09D_temp` with all rows from `decision_table` where `TOUR` starts with `J09D`.\n2. Added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n3. Classified each house:\n   - Default rule: counted distinct `EQUNR` per `HAUS`; `< 3` → `KSA`, otherwise `EVU`.\n   - Overrides applied:\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1` between `500` and `599` → `EVU`\n4. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` on `Installation` = `ANLAGE` to get `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - Joined with `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR`.\n   - Where both sales and net data exist, sales data is used and the corresponding net fields are effectively ignored (the SELECT expression prefers sales values and doesn’t fall back to net when sales is present).\n5. Exported the final result to CSV as `J09D.csv` with exactly these columns:\n\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n\n6. Sent the CSV file to `meter.readings@evu.com` for the EVU team.\n7. Dropped the temporary table `J09D_temp`.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also summarize the row counts by `ENTSCHEIDUNG` for this tour.",
